.TH NOTOLOG 1 "February 2026" "Notolog 1.2.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
notolog \- Markdown editor with AI assistant
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B notolog
.RI [ \-h ]
.RI [ \-v ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B Notolog
is a modern, open-source Markdown editor with AI assistant features, built using Python and PySide6.

It is a graphical desktop application. Run without arguments to launch the GUI.

Features include syntax highlighting, encryption support, on-device LLM integration (ONNX, llama.cpp), and multi-language support.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Display help information and exit.

.TP
.B \-v, \-\-version
Display version information and exit.

.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/Notolog/notolog_editor.conf
User settings file (QSettings).
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/applications/notolog_app_config.toml
Application configuration file.

.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B QT_QPA_PLATFORM
Qt platform plugin (e.g., xcb, wayland).

